Is there a way to filter Google search results?
text:
SEO spam pollutes the top results in google.

One major thing I have noticed is that a lot of companies write an article on "10 best SAAS products in <their industry>" and mentioned there in the list is their own product.

Those articles tend to be biased.

So I was wondering if there was anyway to ignore articles that mentioned their own product in the article when using Google search?

Does anyone use Google Earth Engine?
text:
I work with satellite imagery, and within the satellite / geospatial world I hear a lot about Google Earth Engine as a tool for imagery data processing (especially in academia). Curious how popular GEE is more generally though - does anyone use it or have examples of how it gets used outside of academia?

Thanks for sharing!
